INIA GENTREE practical course on DeltaTraitSDM: modeling tree height from common garden data

An example for tree height measured in European beech network of common gardens

Marta Benito Garzon, Homero Garate Escamilla & Natalia Vizcaino Palomar

Tree height information available at:

BEECHCOSTe52 Network of common gardens: https://zenodo.org/record/1240931#.XZyLvvdS9uQ Robson et al. (2018) Scientific Data

Climate information available at

EUMEDCLIM: https://gentree.data.inra.fr/climate/ Fréjaville & Benito Garzon (2018) Frontiers in Ecology & Evolution

DeltaTraitSDM Approach

Benito Garzon et al. (2019) New Phytologist

Our course is based on the following published models:

Garate Escamilla et al (2019) Global Ecology and Biogeography

Garate Escamilla et al. (2019) Agricultural and Forest Meteorology

##Cross-validation with independent data

### Cross-validation with independent data - to assess capacity of extrapolation of the model
calibrate.data=sample(1:nrow(Fagus), 0.66*nrow(Fagus))
Fagus1=Fagus[calibrate.data,]
Fagus2=Fagus[-calibrate.data,]

M1 <- lmer(log(H) ~ St_Age + St_Pet.max_P + St_Bio13_T + I(St_Pet.max_P^2) + I(St_Bio13_T^2)  
            + St_Age*St_Pet.max_P + St_Age*St_Bio13_T +  St_Pet.max_P*St_Bio13_T 
            + (1|Trial/Block/Tree_ID) + (1|ID_ProvCode), Fagus1)

M2 = predict (M1, newdata=Fagus2,re.form=NA, type="response")

cor.test(Fagus2$H, M2, method = ("pearson"))

mvar1<-rep(mean(var1), length=length(mvar2))
mvar1<-rep(mean(var1), length=length(mvar2))

#select provenances coming from the lowest and highest quantile within the climatic niche 
mvar1_low<-rep(quantile(Fagus$St_Pet.max_P,0.0005), length=length(mvar2))
mvar1_high<-rep(quantile(Fagus$St_Pet.max_P,0.995), length=length(mvar2))

#We fix the age of our trees to 13 years

#average response 
aa<-predict(M20,DFAge13, re.form=NA, type="response")
a <-exp(aa)

#lowest response
DFlowAge13= data.frame("St_Age" = mvar0, "St_Pet.max_P" = mvar1_low, "St_Bio13_T" = mvar2)
alow<-predict(M20, DFlowAge13, re.form=NA, type="response")
al <-exp(alow)

#highest response
DFhighAge13= data.frame("St_Age" = mvar0, "St_Pet.max_P" = mvar1_high, "St_Bio13_T" = mvar2)
ahigh<-predict(M20, DFhighAge13, re.form=NA, type="response")
ah <-exp(ahigh)

original_mvar2=mvar2*sd(Fagus$bio13_P,na.rm=T)+mean(Fagus$bio13_T,na.rm=T)

#extract coefficients
coef<-fixef(M20)
coef<-as.data.frame(coef)
str(coef)
## 'data.frame':    9 obs. of  1 variable:
##  $ coef: num  4.8439 0.6446 0.0258 0.097 -0.0127 ...
#write the prediction function 

predH<-function(Age, var_Pop, var_Trial)  
{    
  
  var_Trial2 <- var_Trial*var_Trial
  var_Pop2 <- var_Pop*var_Pop
  
  Age_var_Pop <- Age*var_Pop
  Age_var_Trial <- Age*var_Trial
  var_Pop_Trial <- var_Trial*var_Pop
  
  
  coef[1,]+
    coef[2,]*(Age)+
    coef[3,]*(var_Pop)+
    coef[4,]*(var_Trial)+
    coef[5,]*(var_Pop2)+
    coef[6,]*(var_Trial2)+
    coef[7,]*(Age_var_Pop)+
    coef[8,]*(Age_var_Trial)+
    coef[9,]*(var_Pop_Trial) 
}

St_Bio13_T <- Bio13_T_Tst
rsmean <- stack(St_Age, St_Pet.max_P, St_Bio13_T)
names(rsmean)=c("St_Age","St_Pet.max_P","St_Bio13_T")
names(rsmean)
## [1] "St_Age"       "St_Pet.max_P" "St_Bio13_T"
predAge10 <- predict(rsmean, M20, re.form = NA, type='response')
#predAgemean <- predHeight(Age=St_Age, var_Pop=St_Pet.max_P, var_Trial=St_Bio13_T)

predH_Age10<- exp(predAge10)

plot (predH_Age10, main="Tree height predited at age = 10")

#### Mask
PredHAge_10<- mask(predH_Age10, FagusDistr) 
plot(PredHAge_10, xlim = c(-10, 45), ylim = c(35, 65), main="Tree height prediction at age = 10 within beech range for current climatic conditions")
plot(europe, add=T)

##Predict future distribution of tree height under the RCP 8.5. scenario

Bio13F<-raster("/home/marta/Desktop/INIA - GENTREE Methods in Forest Conservation Genetics/H/bio13_RCP8.5.tif")
Bio13F_T <- crop(Bio13F, newext)
Bio13F_T_Tst <- scale(Bio13F_T, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE)
plot(Bio13F_T_Tst,  main="Max Temperature of Warmest Month - RCP 8.5. 2080")

rsmean <- stack(St_Age, St_Pet.max_P, Bio13F_T_Tst)
names(rsmean)=c("St_Age","St_Pet.max_P","St_Bio13_T")
names(rsmean)
## [1] "St_Age"       "St_Pet.max_P" "St_Bio13_T"
predAge10 <- predict(rsmean, M20, re.form = NA, type='response')
#predAgemean <- predHeight(Age=St_Age, var_Pop=St_Pet.max_P, var_Trial=St_Bio13_T)

predAge10<- exp(predAge10)

plot (predAge10, main="Tree height predited at age = 10 under RCP 8.5. 2080")

PredAge_10<- mask(predAge10, FagusDistr) #### Mask
plot(PredAge_10, xlim = c(-10, 45), ylim = c(35, 65),  main="Tree height prediction at age = 10 within beech range for 2080 RCP 8.5.")
plot  (europe, add=T)
